The paper focuses on improving speech recognition accuracy by incorporating visual information, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and end-to-end models, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of adaptive training, which could fall under the category of speech processing (cs.SD).
